###How to fix the App Dependencies issue of minimist:1.2.5 of pkg:npm/minimist@1.2.5 in apache web server and which owasp top 10 web 2021 category this issue belong to ?
To fix the App Dependencies issue of minimist:1.2.5 of pkg:npm/minimist@1.2.5 in Apache web server, you can follow these steps:

1. Update the minimist dependency to a newer version. You can do this by running the following command:

```
npm install minimist@latest
```

2. Restart the Apache web server.

The minimist:1.2.5 dependency is vulnerable to a security vulnerability that could allow an attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system. This vulnerability is a remote code execution (RCE) vulnerability, which is a serious security vulnerability that can allow an attacker to take complete control of a system.

The OWASP Top 10 Web 2021 category for this issue is A1 - Injection. Injection flaws, such as RCE vulnerabilities, are the most common web application security vulnerabilities. They occur when unvalidated or unfiltered user input is used to control the execution of code.

Here are some additional steps you can take to improve the security of your Apache web server:

* Keep all software up to date. This includes the Apache web server itself, as well as any third-party libraries or plugins that you use.
* Use a web application firewall (WAF). A WAF can help to protect your web server from common web attacks, such as SQL injection and cross-site scripting (XSS).
* Implement a content security policy (CSP). A CSP can help to prevent attackers from injecting malicious code into your web pages.
* Use strong passwords and enable two-factor authentication for all administrative accounts.
* Regularly scan your web server for vulnerabilities. You can use a variety of tools to do this, such as Nessus or QualysGuard.

By following these steps, you can help to improve the security of your Apache web server and protect it from attack.
